snippet: The Washington Redskins and the Dallas Cowboys will each be docked millions of dollars in salary-cap space - $36 million for the Redskins, $10 million for the Cowboys - because they dumped salaries in 2010 despite league warnings.
abstract: The Washington Redskins and the Dallas Cowboys will each be docked millions of dollars in salary-cap space - $36 million for the Redskins, $10 million for the Cowboys - because they dumped salaries in 2010 despite league warnings.

headline.main: Penalties for Redskins and Cowboys Will Cost Them Cap Space
